# Table Column Sizing Rule

Tables must show full cell content on **one line** unless a column is explicitly marked for multi-line content (e.g. automation rule chips).

## Principles

1. **Size columns to content** — use `minmax(max-content, …)` in CSS grids, or `table-layout: auto` for `<table>`.
2. **No default truncation** — `.data-grid__cell` does not ellipsis. Use `.data-grid__cell--truncate` only when product explicitly accepts crop + `title` tooltip.
3. **No accidental wrap** — avoid fixed pixel columns narrower than header labels or typical data. Do not use `.data-grid__cell--wrap` for single-value text columns.
4. **Horizontal scroll over crop** — `.data-grid` scrolls horizontally (`overflow-x: auto`). Wide tables scroll inside the pane; do not clip with `overflow-hidden` on the grid wrapper.
5. **Future zoom** — horizontal/vertical table zoom will adjust density; column mins should be content-based so zoom scales readable text instead of revealing hidden overflow.

## CSS grid tables

```html
<div class="data-grid">
  <div class="data-grid__header"
    style="grid-template-columns: minmax(140px, 1fr) minmax(96px, max-content) 48px;">
    <span class="data-grid__header-cell">Long Header Label</span>
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li class="data-grid__row"
      style="grid-template-columns: minmax(140px, 1fr) minmax(96px, max-content) 48px;">
      <span class="data-grid__cell">Value</span>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
```

- Match `grid-template-columns` on header and every row.
- Prefer `minmax(Npx, max-content)` for label/numeric columns sized to header text.
- Action/menu columns: fixed `40px`–`48px`.

## HTML `<table>` tables

```html
<div class="data-grid">
  <table class="data-grid-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Transaction ID</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody><tr><td>{{ id }}</td></tr></tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

- Do **not** use `table-fixed` unless every column width is verified against content.
- Remove `truncate` / `text-ellipsis` from `<td>` unless using opt-in `data-grid-table__cell--truncate`.
- Sticky columns: use `min-w-[…]` instead of fixed `w-[…]` when content varies.

## Explicit multi-line columns

Use `.data-grid__cell--wrap` or `.data-grid-table--relaxed` only when the design requires chips, stacked lines, or composite cell content — not for long plain strings.

## Checklist before merge

- [ ] Header labels fully visible
- [ ] Longest row value fully visible (or horizontal scroll present)
- [ ] No unintended second-line wraps in standard data cells
- [ ] Row action menus not clipped (`overflow-hidden` removed from grid when menus exist)
